    <note>Sun(1) Lan [1535] An ancestor moved from Yangzhou, Jiangdu county to Gaoyou. His uncle, an elder cousin, a younger cousin, and his sister's son, Wu(3) Guan (not in dataset), all entered the civil service via his yin. The notice of Jue as Hubu shilang in 1095 (XCB:SB, 12.17b) refers to Lan, who was assigned to post as prefect of Taiyuan when he disagreed with Cai Jing (Hubu shangshu [1094-6]) over the hired-service system. He was Jue's [1521] younger brother and Wang(2) Yue(1)'s [1933] son-in-law. His son, Si [3782], was Wang(2) Yue(1)'s grandson-in-law. XCB, 305.10a-10b, 313.8a, 340.5b, 347.1b, 370.10a; Bi Zhongyou, WJ, 13.7b-13b. CBD, 3, 1912-3.</note>
